<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="482" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[113,1089,220,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,241,508,531]" pageId="9" pageNumber="482">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curler &amp; Priyadarsanan &amp; Atree" authorityYear="2015" box="[405,503,508,531]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Saximormia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladiator">
<emphasis box="[405,503,508,531]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="482">gladiator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning “swordsman” in reference to the conspicuous, spathiform (sword-like) setae on the male gonostyli. Noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[113,665,572,595]" pageId="9" pageNumber="482" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[113,1089,220,787]" box="[113,665,572,595]" pageId="9" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,260,572,595]" pageId="9" pageNumber="482">Distribution.</emphasis>
Recorded only from the 
<typeStatus box="[527,573,572,595]" pageId="9" pageNumber="482">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="482" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[113,1089,220,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,243,604,627]" pageId="9" pageNumber="482">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curler &amp; Priyadarsanan &amp; Atree" authorityYear="2015" box="[249,483,604,627]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Saximormia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladiator">
<emphasis box="[249,483,604,627]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="482">Saximormia gladiator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represents the first record of this genus for 
<collectingCountry box="[944,1001,604,627]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="482">India</collectingCountry>
, and the westernmost record for the Oriental Region. Only three species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Jezek, 1984" authorityName="Jezek" authorityYear="1984" box="[826,1088,636,659]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Saximormia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[826,955,636,659]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="482">Saximormia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="JEZEK J." box="[962,1088,636,659]" pageId="9" pageNumber="482" pagination="155 - 171" refId="ref4531" refString="JEZEK J. 1984: Nomenclatorical changes of some higher taxa of palaearctic Psychodinae (Diptera, Psychodidae). Acta Faunistica Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 17: 155 - 171." type="journal article" year="1984">Ježek, 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
have previously been described (
<bibRefCitation author="JEZEK J." box="[453,574,668,691]" pageId="9" pageNumber="482" pagination="235 - 252" refId="ref4596" refString="JEZEK J. 2010: Further new taxa of non-biting moth flies (Diptera: Psychodidae: Psychodinae) from Malaysia. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 50: 235 - 252." type="journal article" year="2010">JEŽEK 2010</bibRefCitation>
), and while their morphology is generally similar, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curler &amp; Priyadarsanan &amp; Atree" authorityYear="2015" box="[113,240,700,723]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Saximormia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladiator">
<emphasis box="[113,240,700,723]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="482">S. gladiator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly unique due to the presence of prominent setae on the gonostyli. Few specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curler &amp; Priyadarsanan &amp; Atree" authorityYear="2015" box="[261,387,732,755]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Saximormia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="482" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladiator">
<emphasis box="[261,387,732,755]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="482">S. gladiator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were available for study, and those that were did not slide mount in a way that was entirely conducive to studying genitalic morphology.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
